I don't have enough gear to experiment with this, but I sure wish someone with a stopwatch and two Flowing thought I items would take the time to carefully verify what's true.  For accuracy be sure and time things while you are standing up and not medding as the FT effect will be much clearer. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugoladus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Goladus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/22/01 12:10:57 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: FT stacking:  Is there consensus</span><hr size=1> If you ever get a flowing thought item, perform the following test several times:<br>
<br>
Turn eqlog.txt on with /log on<br>
<br>
Cast spells until you are oom(use your lowest level nuke to make sure you get rid of it all).<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Stand</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, let your mana regenerate naturally, and start attempting to cast a spell(an unspecialized spell.  Minor shielding maybe).  When you can cast the spell, you'll have some data.  You'll also be oom again, so I suggest repeating the test a few times to get mroe accurate results.  When you are done, you should have the following data:<br>
<br>
M = Mana cost from the spell<br>
S = Standing time needed to regen that much mana.<br>
<br>
M/S = Mana regained per second<br>
<br>
Multiply M/S by 6 to get an estimate of mana per tick.<br>
<br>
Do this with each level of flowing thought item that you have, including none at all, and repeat the test many times.<br>
<br>
Expected results for a non-stacking scenerio<br>
<br>
No item = 1<br>
FT1 = 2<br>
FT1+FT1 = 2<br>
FT2 = 3<br>
FT1+FT2 = 3<br>
<br>
Expected results for a stacking scenerio<br>
<br>
No item = 1<br>
FT1 = 2<br>
FT1+FT1 = 3<br>
FT2 = 3<br>
FT1+FT2 = 4<br>
<br>
